AS PASSED SENATE
A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Chapter 30 of Title 43 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
2 optometrists, so as to provide for doctors of optometry to dispense and sell pharmaceutical
3 agents to patients under certain conditions; to provide for related matters; to provide for an
4 effective date; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
5 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
6 SECTION 1.
7 Chapter 30 of Title 43 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to optometrists,
8 is amended by revising subparagraph (H) of paragraph (2) of Code Section 43-30-1, relating
9 to definitions, as follows:
10 "(H)(i) Nothing in this chapter shall be construed to allow a A doctor of optometry
11 to may dispense and sell pharmaceutical agents, other than controlled substances, that
12 are related to the treatment of diseases and conditions of the eye and adnexa oculi and
13 are for a legitimate medical purpose to patients provided that a doctor of optometry
14 shall:
15 (I) Be on the premises when any pharmaceutical agent is dispensed to a patient and
16 be actively involved in the dispensing process;
