17 (II) Inform the patient on the appropriate use of the pharmaceutical agent being
18 dispensed;
19 (III) Document in the patient's record the name, strength, quantity, and appropriate
20 use of the pharmaceutical agent dispensed; and
21 (IV) Maintain a readily retrievable record system by manual or electronic means
22 of all the pharmaceutical agents purchased for administration, dispensing, or selling
23 in the course of the professional practice.
24 (ii) Nothing in this subparagraph shall expand the administrative or prescriptive
25 authority of a doctor of optometry."
26 SECTION 2.
27 Said chapter is further amended by revising subsection (a) of Code Section 43-30-13, relating
28 to construction of chapter, as follows:
29 "(a) Nothing in this chapter shall be construed to apply to physicians and surgeons duly
30 licensed to practice medicine, nor; to prevent persons from selling spectacles or eyeglasses
31 on prescription from any duly qualified optometrist or physician, nor; to prevent any person
32 from selling glasses as articles of merchandise or from using test cards in connection with
33 the sale of such glasses at a permanently located place when not trafficking or attempting
34 to traffic upon assumed skill in optometry; nor shall anything in this chapter be construed
35 or to authorize any registered optometrist to use, dispense, sell, prescribe, or administer
36 drugs except as permitted by law or, to practice medicine or surgery in any manner as
37 defined by the laws of this state; nor shall this chapter be construed to authorize any such
38 person , or to use the title of 'M.D.' or any other title mentioned in Code Section 43-34-21
39 or 43-34-22."
